'''discriminant''' (''plural'' '''discriminants''')

#(''mathematics'') An [[expression]] that gives information about the [[root]]s of a [[polynomial]]; for example, the [[expression]] ''D = b<sup>2</sup> - 4ac'' determines whether the [[root]]s of the [[quadratic equation]] ''ax<sup>2</sup> + bx + c = 0'' are [[real]] and [[distinct]] (''D'' > 0), real and [[equal]] (''D'' = 0) or [[complex]] (''D'' < 0).

